en=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Jan 18, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104qnd1705582899319.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/qnd1705582899319.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/qnd1705582899319.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"kpg1665702809716\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                             \n Using Glyphs \n      \n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">You can use glyphs in form components and widgets, panels, menus, and drag-and-drop formats.\n </p>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step\" id=\"kpg1665702809716__li_d6293e1_d6294e1_d6295e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">To use a glyph for an operation button in a Panel, select the glyph in the Panel's <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Glyph Name</span> property.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"kpg1665702809716__li_d6296e1_d6297e1_d6298e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">To use a glyph as an icon on a Command Button, Picture, Drag Source, or Drop Target widget:\n </span>\n<ol class=\"ol substeps\" type=\"a\">\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"kpg1665702809716__li_d6299e1_d6300e1_d6301e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Set the field's <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Data Type</span> to <code class=\"ph codeph\">Image (glyph)</code>\n                                   The Windows command button does not support images within the command button. If you want image functionality in command buttons, set <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Representation</span> to <code class=\"ph codeph\">Uniface</code>.\n                                 </span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"kpg1665702809716__li_d6302e1_d6303e1_d6304e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"kpg1665702809716__p_d13106e1_d13107e1_d13108e1\">Specify the name of the glyph in the\n                        <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Initial Value</span> property. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">If you load a glyph for which there are a number of variations, Uniface\n                     attempts to load the one with the most suitable size. Microsoft Windows\n                     metafiles are rendered on a bitmap correctly sized before displaying.</div>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"kpg1665702809716__li_d6305e1_d6306e1_d6307e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Optionally, to scale an image to fit a command button, use the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Scale</span> and <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Preserve Aspect</span> properties.\n </span>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"kpg1665702809716__li_d6308e1_d6309e1_d6310e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">To use the glyph as a background image of a Form, Entity, or Windows Application Shell, specify the glyph in the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Background Image</span> property or the object.\n </span>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cpe1705582470714.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Create and Maintain Glyphs</a><p>Glyphs are maintained and deployed in a runtime library.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5830586\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5830586\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Using Glyphs Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 18, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Using Glyphs You can use glyphs in form components and widgets, panels, menus, and drag-and-drop formats. To use a glyph for an operation button in a Panel, select the glyph in the Panel's Glyph Name property. To use a glyph as an icon on a Command Button, Picture, Drag Source, or Drop Target widget: Set the field's Data Type to Image (glyph) The Windows command button does not support images within the command button. If you want image functionality in command buttons, set Representation to Uniface . Specify the name of the glyph in the Initial Value property. If you load a glyph for which there are a number of variations, Uniface attempts to load the one with the most suitable size. Microsoft Windows metafiles are rendered on a bitmap correctly sized before displaying. Optionally, to scale an image to fit a command button, use the Scale and Preserve Aspect properties. To use the glyph as a background image of a Form, Entity, or Windows Application Shell, specify the glyph in the Background Image property or the object. Related Links Create and Maintain Glyphs Glyphs are maintained and deployed in a runtime library. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}